HEADWORD: Ita palm
<hw>I"ta palm`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A magnificent
species of palm (<spn>Mauritia flexuosa</spn>), growing near the
Orinoco. The natives eat its fruit and buds, drink its sap, and make
thread and cord from its fiber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Itch</ent>⟦br⟧
